      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ALTOCUMULUS (4) is rarely far away but tends to find one better, placing 12 from 24 starts. Finished third (26.08) at Murray Bridge last time making it two minors on end. Has a good record at this journey. The form from his last run stacks up well. Overdue and gets his chance. MYAH MISS (1) box seated before sticking on well to finish 4 lengths away in third (17.78) at Mt Gambier in a Grade 6 over 305m. Well placed and gets her chance. NEON BLUE (2) showed little early speed at her last couple, the latest finishing fourth (23.58) in a Grade 6 at Mt Gambier. Solid record at the distance winning two races. Goes well out of this box with a win and three minor placings. Key runner who gets her chance to atone. ZIPPING THERON (8) is a last start winner who can measure up again.",
